Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper focuses on developing a dialogue system for automatic medical diagnosis, which falls under the scope of natural language processing and dialogue systems. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The proposed system uses a novel Knowledge-routed Deep Q-network (KR-DQN) for managing topic transitions, which is a machine learning technique commonly used in AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper heavily relies on data-driven learning and introduces a new machine learning model (KR-DQN) for dialogue management. 
4. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the potential impact of the proposed system on the healthcare industry and society as a whole. 
5. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper incorporates a medical knowledge graph into the dialogue system, which involves database management and knowledge representation.
